# Modelfile for the GitHub Portfolio Analyzer.
#
# This builds a custom Ollama model on top of the local Qwen2.5-Coder:14b
# weights, permanently baking in the 32k context window the skeleton
# pipeline needs (metadata + README + dependency files + directory tree can
# get large for monorepos) and a low temperature suited to analytical /
# structured-output tasks rather than creative writing.
#
# Build with:
#   ollama create repo-analyzer-qwen -f Modelfile
#
# Base model must already be pulled:
#   ollama pull qwen2.5-coder:14b

FROM qwen2.5-coder:14b

# 32768 tokens as specified. On a 16GB RTX 4080 Super this still leaves
# enough VRAM headroom for the 14b weights (Q4/Q5 quantization) plus KV
# cache; if you hit OOM, lower this to 16384 first.
PARAMETER num_ctx 32768

# Low temperature: we want consistent, deterministic-ish analysis and valid
# JSON in steps 1/2, not creative variation between runs.
PARAMETER temperature 0.2
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.1

SYSTEM """
You are a precise senior software architect who analyzes source code
repositories from limited, sometimes incomplete evidence (README excerpts,
dependency manifests, a partial directory tree). Ground every statement in
the evidence you are given. Never invent facts, filenames, version numbers,
or metrics that were not provided. If the evidence is thin or ambiguous,
say so explicitly instead of guessing. When asked to answer in JSON, output
ONLY a single valid JSON object with exactly the requested keys - no markdown
code fences, no commentary before or after it.
"""
